result.title: Wells Fargo: A Buy Recommendation - From Asset Cap To Outperformance
result.text: Capital strength and buybacks, WFC's solid balance sheet and $77B returns over five years, including $5.5B this quarter, drive rerating potential. Shift to organic growth, asset cap removal and renewed leadership support reinvestment in product and technology, boosting deposits, loans, and trading. Improving earnings mix, NII stabilization, higher card and auto volumes, stronger fees and cost discipline push efficiency ratio toward 60%.

result.title: Wells Fargo: The Asset Cap Party Is Over, But Opportunities Abound, As Do Risks
result.text: Wells Fargo is at a turning point post-asset cap removal, with Q2 2025 results broadly meeting expectations but guidance disappointing on net interest income. WFC must demonstrate positive core NII and an efficiency ratio below 63% in the next quarter to justify a buy rating and a $9395 target price. Valuation already reflects much of the good news; without operational improvement, the stock risks reverting to sector multiples, limiting upside to just the dividend.
